snippet.title: Amber Heard's cuts and bruises 'potentially caused by Musk not Depp'
snippet.description: Amber Heard's cuts and bruises to her face she obtained during the end of her relationship with Johnny Depp appeared when she had been "interacting with" Elon Musk and not while she was with the Pirates of the Caribbean actor, building staff at Heard and Depp's LA penthouse have claimed in court. ¬†The allegations were made in a sworn video statement made by Trinity Esparza who worked in the exclusive building, which housed Depp and Heard's penthouse. ¬†She said under oath that she saw no injuries to Heard's face after Depp allegedly "threw a mobile phone at her like a baseball player" in a row that is claimed to have taken place on May 21.Esparza, who owned the company responsible for the concierge service at the property, told London's High Court that she saw Heard throughout the following week of the alleged incident but saw no bruises or cuts on the actress.She adds that Heard was often not wearing makeup.Esparza said: "She never wore makeup... Very rarely.   ¬†"She had a beautiful complexion."Six days after the alleged fight, she says Heard sported "a red cut underneath her right eye and red marks by her eye" on May 27, 2016.Esparza went on to allege that two weeks after Depp left the Penthouse on June 4, she saw Heard with more injuries.She claims Heard had a bruise on either side of her neck "in the shape of fingers and a bruise on her left cheek".Probed by Depp's legal team as to the location of the defendant during this time, Esparza replied: "Out of the country."   ¬†Asked as to whom Heard had been "interacting with" during this time, she simply added: "Elon Musk."Asked if there was anybody else, she replied: "No."Two months later (July 2016), Esparza said she saw Elon Musk go to the building to visit Ms Heard.While Musk was there she said she noticed marks on Heard's body ‚Äì the "left side".She may also have seen a "band aid".The Sun's QC Wass probed: "You want to suggest that Elon Musk must have injured her?"   ¬†Esparza added: "I didn't suggest that. I don't know what happened." ¬†Adam Waldman, Depp's lawyer, said: "Johnny Depp left the country after Ms Heard's most notorious abuse hoax where she claimed he threw a phone into her right eye. Yet two weeks later, the head concierge at the building testified she saw Ms Heard with a bruise under her other eye, finger shaped bruises on her throat and a bandaged arm."It was Elon Musk who had been coming up to Mr Depp's penthouse during his two-week absence."

snippet.title: K-Punk: The Collected and Unpublished Writings of Mark Fisher
snippet.description:
Join Repeater Books for a discussion of Mark Fisher‚Äôs work with the novelist Hari Kunzru, Chapo Trap House co-host Amber A‚ÄôLee Frost, writer Sukhdev Sandhu, and musician Meredith Graves.

Book launch for ‚ÄúK-Punk: The Collected and Unpublished Writings of Mark Fisher,‚Äù published by Repeater Books. Filmed at Verso Books in Brooklyn on November 28, 2018.

When Mark Fisher committed suicide in 2017 at the age of 48, we lost one of the twenty-first century‚Äôs greatest cultural theorists. An icon for today‚Äôs insurgent ‚Äúalt-left,‚Äù from 2003 to 2016 Fisher wrote dazzling analyses of our strange and terrifying world‚Äîneoliberalism, the loneliness and distracted boredom of digital life, and how these realities are reflected in music, film, TV, and literature. He also developed a vision of a different future‚Äîbased on community, democratic control of the economy, creative freedom for all, and harnessing technology for the good of humanity.

‚ÄúK-Punk‚Äù collects Fisher‚Äôs most incendiary and influential posts from his seminal blog ‚Äúk-punk‚Äù, as well as a selection of his brilliantly insightful film, television and music reviews, together with his extraordinary writings on politics, activism, mental health, and popular modernism for numerous websites and magazines. Also included are two previously unpublished essays, the unfinished introduction to his planned book on ‚ÄúAcid Communism‚Äù, and an analysis of the 2016 US Presidential election, written shortly after Trump‚Äôs victory.

Lastly, I revisit the possibility that the bruises are actually makeup. 

In the end, you be the judge on whether the so called bruises on Heard's face are some sort of skin condition, plastic surgery, or makeup.

snippet.title: Amber Heard Shares Photo of Bruised Face, Claims Johnny Depp Tried to Pay Her Off
snippet.description:

snippet.title: Witnesses claim Amber Heard had no facial bruising days after alleged Johnny Depp attack
snippet.description:
Witnesses claim Amber Heard had no facial bruising days after alleged Johnny Depp attack 

info

 Two witnesses claim Amber Heard had no bruising on her face days after Johnny Depp allegedly attacked her in their home, according to US reports.

Amber filed for divorce last month after 15 months of marriage and subsequently claimed the actor had assaulted her during a row on May 21.

The concierges in the pair's building claim there didn't appear to be any evidence of facial bruising when they saw the actress on Monday, two days after the alleged incident, reports TMZ.

The website says a lawyer who lives in the building was told by a concierge that her face looked so flawless, "I was about to compliment her on her complexion
